NODEPORT
--------

> host port as we do in docker 
> used for nonprod
> to expose pod to internet

internet -> node ip:<nodeport> -> SERVICE (lable selector) -> routes to POD equals to lable selector -> container

nodeport : is the external node to access internal node

say x.x.x.x:30001  => mapped to  => SERVICE IP and internal port/backend port
internal port will be container image port
for nginx -> 80
for tomcat -> 8080

> lable selector





CLUSTER IP
----------

> internal communication


LOAD BALANCER
-------------

> this actaully creates ELB in AWS and maps to node port
> used to expose pod to internet 
> used mostly for prod activities




